@Seequ: For the sites, initially I entered them all by hand. However, Kaffiene has a set of python tools I developed to help pull sites from around ZeroNet. Those can be found if you click on 'scripts' or check out the Kaffiene github repo. For the ZeroMe profiles, it's a new script I wrote (not pushed yet), that once again fetches them and compiles them into a document for searching.

I'm wondering if there's a way to do the ZeroMe profiles with just javascript, so I don't have to focus on updating, like how the various off-site indexes work. I'd need access to the merged-zerome/zerome.db database to do so. But that's pretty big at 30mb for mine (with all the hubs) whereas the profile index is at only 700kb.

The "backend" is just me haha. No fancy bots/crawlers/taggers/whatever yet. That's on the agenda and why Kaffiene's index hasn't been updated in months. If you check the dropdown menu you can look at the untagged sites the scripts found. I don't have a way of automatically tagging them yet. That's a WIP. Once I get that done though it'll be smooth sailing.

@Zaira: I'm just reading from the merged zerome db using a quick python script I wrote up. The tools I used to do this will be put on my github once I commit/push. This is the SQL I used to generate the list in the picture: `SELECT user_name, count(user_name) FROM follow GROUP by user_name ORDER BY count(user_name) desc` Reading from the database found at `/1MeFqFfFFGQfa1J3gJyYYUvb5Lksczq7nH/merged-ZeroMe/ZeroMe.db` in your data folder.

As for the total number of *active* users, that's impossible to say. How do you define 'active'. As for the total, I think I saw that there's somewhere around 6-7000 zerome users, and probably more zeronet users.

@Flyman: That was originally what I was working on. I wanted to come up with a list of people who followed me. Then once I realized I could get this list and thus number easily, I went ahead and tried to get a list of who the most followed user is (who happens to be nofish, with me in second). Both scripts will be available soon. If there's enough demand to see followers, I'll go ahead and make a new Zite dedicated for it, since the javascript side of things will need to be a merger site. As for Kaffiene, the plan is to sort ZeroMe users by number of followers so you can find the most popular users quickly.

